cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep neural network for automated whole slide image tagging in histopathology. This involves image analysis and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method also involves attention mechanisms and learning patch characteristics, which are common in natural language processing (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of whole slide images suggests a potential application in medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category.
